On S&aacute;nchez, Wenger said: &ldquo;I&rsquo;ve worked on transfers for 30 years, so it is likely to happen. But these kind of things are never guaranteed. It&rsquo;s now in the next 24 to 48 hours that it will happen or not.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Wenger was asked whether Mkhitaryan was primed to arrive as part of the S&aacute;nchez transfer. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s my understanding, yes,&rdquo; he said. &ldquo;The wages would not be a problem. This would be an exchange of players and I think one would replace the other. Are we still on the transfer market after that? Yes.&rdquo;
